- cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the problem of constrained bandwidth and proposes a solution that involves compression and streaming. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses different measures of description complexity within the Chomsky hierarchy of languages. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is another possible category as the paper mentions language complexity and the Chomsky hierarchy. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper discusses the problem of degraded communication and storage capacity. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also a less likely category, but possible as the paper proposes a solution to a practical problem involving mobile networks and communication capacity.
